::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050806-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 120.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Haha, she's the owner of the Express. We joke around calling Pom-Pom the conductor, but everyone knows Himeko is the boss.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 121.ogg}} '''Welt:''' It all started with her encounter with the Astral Express, and they haven't been apart since then.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 122.ogg}} '''Welt:''' She's... extremely passionate, like a burning sun. However, she remains mysterious most of the time. Once in a while, you feel that she's burning herself out trying to accomplish her dream.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 123.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Only someone like her is worthy of the Astral Express. I think Himeko's vision of her whole life revolves around... a very important dream.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Pom-Pom...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050811-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 124.ogg}} '''Welt:''' To be honest, I don't know when Pom-Pom appeared... I think it was before I came to the Express? No wait, maybe it was after...
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 125.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Pom-Pom is like the spirit of the Astral Express. Whenever anyone on the Express needs help, they will appear immediately. It would be ill-advised to underestimate them.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 126.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Pom-Pom is terrifying when they get angry... Yes, terrifying...
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Dan Heng...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050815-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 127.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Dan Heng is a lonely child. He may appear distant and cold, but his heart is kind. Perhaps, he's the way he is today because he spent so much time on the run. Sometimes, he reminds me of myself when I was young...
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 128.ogg}} '''Welt:''' We don't know what he's running from. He once told me that he didn't know either. All he knew was that something was chasing him and that he had to run away &mdash; first from the Xianzhou, then the IPC.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 129.ogg}} '''Welt:''' So he boarded the ship of a troupe called the "Mourning Actors" and escaped the IPC. After a while he made his way to the Express, and he's stayed here longer than anywhere else.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 130.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Don't worry, no matter who or what wants to hurt Dan Heng, we won't let them. Those who dare attack members of the Astral Express should be prepared to suffer the wrath of me and Himeko.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About March 7th...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050820-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 131.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Did Himeko tell you about March 7th? She was trapped in ice, floating through space. We happened upon her and rescued her.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 132.ogg}} '''Welt:''' It was a unique type of ice known as Six-Phased Ice &mdash; a substance that adheres to Imaginary Law, meaning that external forces cannot change its form.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 133.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Whoever sealed her inside the Six-Phased Ice... No matter who it is... did so either to protect or banish her. I believe she had been floating through space for some time.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Return}} I have another question...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_100050307_83-->
:::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Stellarons...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050825-->
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 134.ogg}} '''Welt:''' It's impossible to trace the origin of this phenomenon. When it's observed by humans &mdash; or I should say once it begins to affect the physical world &mdash; it's already too late to reverse.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 135.ogg}} '''Welt:''' It's like a sudden storm that appears on a calm ocean. This phenomenon causes the smooth journey through the expanse to be filled with dangers.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 136.ogg}} '''Welt:''' The mechanism whereby this mutation and corrosion spreads is the Stellarons.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 137.ogg}} '''Welt:''' It promulgated rapidly like cancer cells, so the Interastral Peace Corporation named it the Cancer of All Worlds.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Antimatter Legion...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050830-->
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 138.ogg}} '''Welt:''' They are an army ruled by the Aeon of Destruction, Nanook.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 139.ogg}} '''Welt:''' As Nanook's followers, they stand against all life and civilization and execute the will of Destruction, disseminating chaos and calamity.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 140.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Their actions cannot be explained by reason, because their only motivation and purpose is to destroy.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Fragmentum...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050834-->
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 141.ogg}} '''Welt:''' The Fragmentums are a phenomenon of corrosion.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 142.ogg}} '''Welt:''' The mainstream school of thought is that Stellarons catalyzed the appearance of Fragmentums.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 143.ogg}} '''Welt:''' All matter and space that comes into contact with the Fragmentum will be turned into Fragmentum creations.
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 144.ogg}} '''Welt:''' However, you don't have to feel too burdened. At the very least, the current state of the Stellaron in your body is very stable and will not cause distortion to the outside.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
