:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 135.ogg}} '''Welt:''' It's like a sudden storm that appears on a calm ocean. This phenomenon causes the smooth journey through the expanse to be filled with dangers.
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 136.ogg}} '''Welt:''' The mechanism whereby this mutation and corrosion spreads is the Stellarons.
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 137.ogg}} '''Welt:''' It promulgated rapidly like cancer cells, so the Interastral Peace Corporation named it the Cancer of All Worlds.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Antimatter Legion...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050830-->
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 138.ogg}} '''Welt:''' They are an army ruled by the Aeon of Destruction, Nanook.
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 139.ogg}} '''Welt:''' As Nanook's followers, they stand against all life and civilization and execute the will of Destruction, disseminating chaos and calamity.
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 140.ogg}} '''Welt:''' Their actions cannot be explained by reason, because their only motivation and purpose is to destroy.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Fragmentum...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050834-->
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 141.ogg}} '''Welt:''' The Fragmentums are a phenomenon of corrosion.
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 142.ogg}} '''Welt:''' The mainstream school of thought is that Stellarons catalyzed the appearance of Fragmentums.
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 143.ogg}} '''Welt:''' All matter and space that comes into contact with the Fragmentum will be turned into Fragmentum creations.
:::{{A|VO chapter0 7 welt 144.ogg}} '''Welt:''' However, you don't have to feel too burdened. At the very least, the current state of the Stellaron in your body is very stable and will not cause distortion to the outside.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I don't have any other questions.
