::::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_599000201_156-->
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the history of the galaxy...
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000245-->
:::::::'''Welt:''' There are many gaps in the history of the galaxy, which extend far beyond the limits of human cognition. Moreover, the Aeon Enigmata is going around destroying precious historical records everywhere.
:::::::'''Welt:''' It is said that there was a huge gap in the records between the birth of the universe and when Aeons appeared. During that time, strange existences known as Leviathans roamed.
:::::::'''Welt:''' However, Leviathans disappeared when the Aeons were born. Legend has it that Oroboros the Voracity was the last remaining Leviathan, but no one knows if that's true.
:::::::'''Welt:''' The most ancient Aeon, Qlipoth, gave birth to the Interastral Peace Corporation. From then on, we have the modern history of the galaxy &mdash; but before then, the records are incomplete.
::::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Aeons...
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000250-->
:::::::'''Welt:''' Oh, I love this topic! Honestly, what are Aeons?
:::::::'''Welt:''' I once confused the enemy of my home with the Aeons, but I soon discovered the two are different in nature. An Overlord in the Antimatter Legion can incinerate entire star systems, while their Calamity Vanguards are perfectly capable of destroying a planet by themselves.
:::::::'''Welt:''' Aeons are so powerful that they're near invincible. Long before the Destruction existed, a swarm disaster from the Propagation spread through the stars, and the war between the Abundance and the Hunt has also ruined many worlds.
:::::::'''Welt:''' At least one rule is certain: Aeons can only operate according to their Primum Mobile. For example, we won't ever have to worry about the Harmony stirring up a storm.
