:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Welt's past...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000227-->
::::'''Welt:''' My past? Sorry to disappoint you, but I'm just an ordinary white-collar employee.
::::'''Welt:''' Back home, I worked as a concept artist at an animation studio.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_599000201_136-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_599000201_136-->
:::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Welt's powers...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000230-->
:::::'''Welt:''' Long story short, my powers come from an older acquaintance. You can say I inherited his mission and will.
:::::'''Welt:''' I can mimic anything as long as I understand its principles, which is useful for work. As for black holes... that's an even longer story.
:::::'''Welt:''' I'll tell you about it some other time.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Welt's friends...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000234-->
:::::'''Welt:''' My friends are far away... I hope to find a way back home with the Astral Express' help. People are waiting for me to go back, after all.
:::::'''Welt:''' But this isn't something that can be solved with impatience. There aren't many ways to travel between worlds, and the Astral Express has graciously accepted me.
:::::'''Welt:''' I've asked Madam Herta to send a signal to my home. If my family receives my message, they will know that I am safe.
:::::'''Welt:''' Now, my friends are the Express, the Crew... and you, of course.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Welt's enemies...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000239-->
:::::'''Welt:''' Enemies? I've taken care of my past enemies.
:::::'''Welt:''' If I have to say, my current enemies are Nanook, the Stellaron, and the Antimatter Legion.
:::::'''Welt:''' I want to protect the beauty of this world from those that follow the Path of Destruction.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Return}} I have another question...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_599000201_111-->
:::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About companions...
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000205-->
::::::'''Welt:''' About everyone on the Express? Who would you like to know about?
::::::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_599000201_114-->
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_599000201_114-->
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Himeko...
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000207-->
:::::::'''Welt:''' Haha, she's the owner of the Express. We joke around calling Pom-Pom the conductor, but everyone knows Himeko is the boss.
:::::::'''Welt:''' It all started with her encounter with the Astral Express, and they haven't been apart since then.
:::::::'''Welt:''' She's... extremely passionate, like a burning sun. However, she remains mysterious most of the time. Once in a while, you feel that she's burning herself out trying to accomplish her dream.
:::::::'''Welt:''' Only someone like her is worthy of the Astral Express. I think Himeko's vision of her whole life revolves around... a very important dream.
::::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Pom-Pom...
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000212-->
:::::::'''Welt:''' To be honest, I don't know when Pom-Pom appeared... I think it was before I came to the Express? No wait, maybe it was after...
:::::::'''Welt:''' Pom-Pom is like the spirit of the Astral Express. Whenever anyone on the Express needs help, they will appear immediately. It would be ill-advised to underestimate them.
:::::::'''Welt:''' Pom-Pom is terrifying when they get angry... Yes, terrifying...
::::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Dan Heng...
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000216-->
:::::::'''Welt:''' Dan Heng is a lonely child. He may appear distant and cold, but his heart is kind. Perhaps, he's the way he is today because he spent so much time on the run. Sometimes, he reminds me of myself when I was young...
:::::::'''Welt:''' We don't know what he's running from. He once told me that he didn't know either. All he knew was that something was chasing him and that he had to run away &mdash; first from the Xianzhou, then the IPC.
:::::::'''Welt:''' So he boarded the ship of a troupe called the "Mourning Actors" and escaped the IPC. After a while he made his way to the Express, and he's stayed here longer than anywhere else.
:::::::'''Welt:''' Don't worry, no matter who or what wants to hurt Dan Heng, we won't let them. Those who dare attack members of the Astral Express should be prepared to suffer the wrath of me and Himeko.
::::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About March 7th...
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_599000221-->
:::::::'''Welt:''' Did Himeko tell you about March 7th? She was trapped in ice, floating through space. We happened upon her and rescued her.
:::::::'''Welt:''' It was a unique type of ice known as Six-Phased Ice &mdash; a substance that adheres to Imaginary Law, meaning that external forces cannot change its form.
:::::::'''Welt:''' Whoever sealed her inside the Six-Phased Ice... No matter who it is... did so either to protect or banish her. I believe she had been floating through space for some time.
::::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
